<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 4:20PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Warren and
northwestern Halifax Counties through 500 PM EDT...
At 420 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Littleton, or 13 miles southwest of Roanoke Rapids, moving east at 20
mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Roanoke Rapids, Warrenton, Halifax, Norlina, Littleton, Weldon,
Macon, Medoc Mountain State Park, Afton and Lake Gaston.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
